<p>President Trump has softened his earlier opposition to the UK’s agreement to transfer sovereignty of the Chagos Archipelago to Mauritius, calling it the “best” deal Prime Minister Keir Starmer could achieve after the two leaders spoke by phone. While supporting the political settlement that covers the archipelago — including the Diego Garcia US-UK military facility — Trump stressed that the United States still has the right to ensure the base’s security, including by military means if needed.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/-dhRtFyyszimHNzCdg3D2fbgFs1RslCooSjoIxuL6bVl8ptKRgMbjLIc9GGyB_-eO19NaEmyOnUethQs99Df1i5ryxR9VwUAUY4nJ_XnwYdduYMqlf5rEH7Vw1nCVDeVZw8YCJp9ByxySTikIPmaF5nDnt0PrAIOrTetWirGVR_Kab415asQ6NW7qccJmZRvGqbZiBc' alt='' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Rhetoric shift: Trump called the handover an act of “great stupidity” last month, but after his call with Starmer he said the arrangement was the “best” the UK prime minister could do.</li><li>Territory framing: The plan would cede sovereignty of the British Indian Ocean Territory (which includes Diego Garcia) to Mauritius, keeping the base at the center of the political debate.</li><li>Deal timing: The UK agreement cited in the coverage was reached in 2025 under Prime Minister Starmer and would cede sovereignty of the Chagos Archipelago to Mauritius.</li><li>Greenland argument: Reporting says Trump has pointed to the Chagos handover as one of the “national security reasons” for arguing the US should acquire Greenland.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Donald Trump: After speaking with Starmer, Trump called the arrangement the “best” deal the UK prime minister could make, while stressing US rights to secure the base. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/feb/05/trump-criticism-chagos-islands-starmer'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Prime Minister Keir Starmer’s government: The UK reached a 2025 agreement to cede sovereignty of the Chagos Archipelago to Mauritius, linked to the territory that includes Diego Garcia. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/trump-says-retains-right-to-militarily-secure-chagos-airbase'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>Mauritius: Under the agreement described in the reports, Mauritius is set to receive sovereignty of the archipelago. (<a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/donald-trump-accepts-uk-deal-on-indian-ocean-islands-with-key-military-base-10955262#publisher=newsstand'>NDTV</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/trump-says-retains-right-to-militarily-secure-chagos-airbase'>Trump says US retains right to ‘militarily’ secure Chagos airbase</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/feb/05/trump-criticism-chagos-islands-starmer'>Trump waters down criticism of UK’s Chagos Islands deal after call with Starmer</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/5/trump-tempers-criticism-of-uks-chagos-islands-deal-after-talk-with-starmer'>Trump tempers criticism of UK’s Chagos Islands deal after talk with Starmer</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/donald-trump-accepts-uk-deal-on-indian-ocean-islands-with-key-military-base-10955262#publisher=newsstand'>Trump Accepts UK Deal On Indian Ocean Islands With Key Military Base</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/the-best-he-could-make-trump-endorses-starmers-chagos-deal-but-insists-i-retain-military-right-13976731.html'>&#x27;The best he could make&#x27;: Trump endorses Starmer&#x27;s Chagos deal, but insists &#x27;I retain military right&#x27;</a> - firstpost.com</li></ul>